# .cursorrules — hermes-agent

## Project Context
Hermes agent fleet platform (v0.13.0). Python, Docker, WSL2 runtime.
30 agents, cron-driven, DeepSeek v4 flash model via Together AI.
Skills-based architecture with tool execution pipeline.

## Core Rules

### Decimal Arithmetic (when scoring)
- If any code touches scoring paths shared with biotech-screener, use `Decimal`.
- Agent orchestration/routing logic may use standard float.

### Point-in-Time Safety
- All dates ISO 8601 (`YYYY-MM-DD`).
- Never call `datetime.now()` in data pipelines. Use explicit `as_of_date`.
- Agent runtime timestamps (logging, scheduling) may use `datetime.now()`.

### Deterministic Output
- Pipeline outputs: sorted keys, content hashes, no side effects.
- Agent responses: best-effort determinism (LLM outputs are inherently stochastic).

## Model Routing
- "llama" / "deepseek" models -> Together API
- "claude" models -> Anthropic SDK
- Routing logic lives in the gateway layer — do not hard-code provider URLs in agents.

## Llama/DeepSeek Prompting Conventions
- IF/THEN chains for conditional logic
- Step numbering for multi-step instructions
- Schema-first output (define JSON shape before asking for content)
- Never ask model to infer data not explicitly provided

## Naming
- Python files: `snake_case.py`
- Config: `snake_case.yaml`
- Skill docs: `SKILL.md` (frontmatter required)
- Agent configs: reference AGENTS.md for canonical names

## Commands
```bash
# Docker
docker compose up -d
docker compose logs -f <service>

# Test
pytest -p no:warnings

# Lint
ruff check .
ruff format --check .
```

## Key Constraints
- Read-only/observe-only defaults for agent-related work.
- No live cron, agent, or production mutation unless explicitly requested.
- No broad refactors. One task per session.
- Skill documents load from disk each run — changes take effect on next invocation.
- Exec allowlist governs which tools agents can use.

## Architecture Notes
- Session lifecycle: skill load -> context build -> LLM call -> tool exec -> response
- Cron jobs managed via system crontab in WSL2
- API gateway: port 52379 (local), relay-connected for remote access
- MCP server: 8 read-only tools, skills + gateway modes

## Anti-Patterns (DO NOT)
1. Hard-code provider URLs in agent code
2. Activate agents/crons without explicit approval
3. Bypass exec allowlist
4. Push red main
5. Expand beyond requested scope
6. Convert prep-only agents into live automations without approval
7. Treat metadata freshness as proof of content freshness
8. Invent project state (branches, PRs, commits) without verification

## File Structure Awareness
- `src/` — core platform code
- `agents/` — agent definitions and configs
- `skills/` — SKILL.md documents
- `docker/` — Dockerfile, compose
- `scripts/` — operational scripts
- `tools/` — tool implementations
